[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpy4px410f[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcms_virtual_profile_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report from running the `cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer` on the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLCMS codebase revealed a stack-buffer-overflow in the function `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/cmspack.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The overflow originates from reading one byte past an on-stack [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer while unpacking pixel data. A patch was submitted that:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Extended `UnrollChunkyBytes` to handle multi-byte samples [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing a new `bytes` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable derived from the input format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adjusted alpha [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“Extra”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m channel handling and pointer arithmetic to multiply [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets by `bytes`.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added safeguards around premultiplied alpha scaling.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inserted a comment in `cmsvirt.c` clarifying that `UnrollChunkyBytes` should now [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly read up to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per sample.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter rebuilding with the patch, the same fuzzer run still produced a [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow at a slightly shifted line in `UnrollChunkyBytes`, indicating[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the patch did not fully eliminate out-of-bounds reads.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer log shows a stack-buffer-overflow in `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcmspack.[0m[1;92mc:130:13[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflowing reference is a one-byte read at `accum[0m[1;39m[[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` where `accum` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoints into a stack-allocated frame in `cmsTransform2DeviceLink`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ASan indicates the access at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m from the base of the stack frame, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutside the bounds of the local array used for `FrmIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`FrmOut`.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Important Observations**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash is triggered during `cmsDoTransform` → `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` → `UnrollChunkyBytes`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The parameters to `UnrollChunkyBytes` include:  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `nChan` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumber of channels[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `Extra` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumber of extra alpha channels[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `Stride` [0m[1;39m([0m[39munused in this routine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The buffer `accum` pointing into on-stack arrays.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow suggests `UnrollChunkyBytes` advances `accum` incorrectly, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading beyond allocated space for certain format combinations.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The diff applied to `src/cmspack.c` and `src/cmsvirt.c` is roughly:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```diff[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   --- a/src/cmspack.c[0m                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   @@ [0m[1;36m-90[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m72[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m90[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m87[0m[39m @@[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   -[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Does almost everything but is slow[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Does chunky unpacking for both [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit and [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit formats.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    static[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    cmsUInt8Number* [0m[1;35mUnrollChunkyBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m,[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                      cmsUInt8Number* accum,[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                      cmsUInt32Number Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +    cmsUInt32Number bytes = [0m[1;35mT_BYTES[0m[1;39m([0m[39minfo->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +        accum += Extra * bytes;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPremul && Extra[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m compute alpha_factor from trailing sample[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[33m...[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   -    for [0m[1;39m([0m[33mi[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < nChan; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < nChan; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         cmsUInt32Number index = DoSwap ? [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnChan-i-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : i;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   -        v = [0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*accum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   -        accum++;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   +        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m read [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m or [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes based on bytes[0m                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run post-patch still reports a stack-buffer-overflow in the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, now at line [0m[1;36m139[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Pointer Arithmetic in UnrollChunkyBytes**: Revisit how `accum` is advanced [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand ensure it never reads beyond the end of the buffer passed in. The interplay of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nChan`, `Extra`, and `bytes` needs tight bounds checks.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **InputFormat Macros**: Verify that `T_BYTES`, `T_CHANNELS`, `T_EXTRA`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`T_SWAPFIRST`, and related format macros are correctly interpreted and consistent [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the size of the `accum` buffer allocated upstream.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Calling Context in cmsTransform2DeviceLink**: Inspect the stack-allocated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marrays [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FrmIn`, `FrmOut`, `LUT`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm the sizes match the maximum data [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnrollChunkyBytes may unpack.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Stride Parameter**: Although unused, `Stride` may have been intended to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgovern per-pixel spacing; check if it should influence how far `accum` can advance.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Edge Cases**: Test scenarios with zero `Extra` channels, single-channel [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput, maximum channel counts, and both [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-bit and [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit formats to cover all [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe continued overflow indicates that additional bounds validation or buffer [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresizing is needed around the unpacking routine.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m518[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35m_cmsHandleExtraChannels[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, in, out, PixelsPerLine, LineCount, Stride[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m520[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Empty buffers for quick memcmp[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmsxform.[0m[1;92mc:521[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m529[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m521[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwIn, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwIn[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m522[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwOut, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwOut[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m523[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m524[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Get copy of zero cache[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m525[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&Cache, &p->Cache, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCache[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m526[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m527[0m[39m:    strideIn = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m528[0m[39m:    strideOut = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m529[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmspack.[0m[1;92mc:113[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m119[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExtraFirst[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:        [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPremul && Extra[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:            alpha_factor = [0m[1;35m_cmsToFixedDomain[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39maccum[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:        accum += Extra;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m119[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmspack.[0m[1;92mc:126[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m134[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[33mi[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < nChan; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:        cmsUInt32Number index = DoSwap ? [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnChan - i - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : i;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:        v = [0m[1;35mFROM_8_TO_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*accum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m131[0m[39m:        v = Reverse ? [0m[1;35mREVERSE_FLAVOR_16[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : v;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m132[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m133[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPremul && alpha_factor > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m134[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Investigate Root Cause  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Analysis of the ASan trace and UnrollChunkyBytes shows that the unpacker now [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly advances its local pointer by `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnChan + Extra[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * bytes` bytes per pixel, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut the **input buffer** allocated on the **caller’s** stack [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsTransform2DeviceLink` within `src/cmsvirt.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was still dimensioned for [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte samples only**. When `bytes == [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m`, UnrollChunkyBytes reads two bytes per [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msample from this buffer and can step past its right edge, triggering the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **UnrollChunkyBytes** now supports up to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte samples and advances its [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`accum` pointer by `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnChan * bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExtra * bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **cmsTransform2DeviceLink** [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `cmsvirt.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m declares `FrmIn` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand likely [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FrmOut`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as `cmsUInt8Number FrmIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, i.e. only enough space for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nChan` bytes. For [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit per-channel input, you need up to `[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m * nChan` bytes.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure point in ASan always occurs at `UnrollChunkyBytes`, reading the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond byte of a [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte sample out of `FrmIn`’s bounds.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. **Enlarge the stack‐allocated input buffer** in `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit can hold up to two bytes per channel plus any extra [0m[1;39m([0m[39malpha[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m channel. Since [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnrollChunkyBytes never operates on more than [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per channel [0m[1;39m([0m[39mby design[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreallocating `FrmIn` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand symmetrically `FrmOut`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to `cmsMAXCHANNELS * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m + [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcmsMAXEXTRA * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m` bytes suffices.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. **Leave UnrollChunkyBytes unchanged**, preserving its correct byte-based [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marithmetic. This respects the new multi-byte logic and retains premultiplied-alpha [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupport.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. **Do not change harness code, fuzzing logic, or external libraries**.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. **Retain existing tests**: expansion of internal buffers will not break any [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality or tests, but rather remove the overflow.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Implementation Steps  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Open `src/cmsvirt.c`, locate the declaration of `FrmIn` and `FrmOut` in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsTransform2DeviceLink`. It will read something like:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt8Number FrmIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt8Number FrmOut[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Adjust these declarations to reserve two bytes per channel plus extra alpha [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mmax [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, for the worst-case of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit samples:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Allow up to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per channel [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plus extra channels[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #define MAX_BYTES_PER_SAMPLE [0m[1;36m2[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt8Number FrmIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS * MAX_BYTES_PER_SAMPLE + cmsMAXEXTRA * [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_BYTES_PER_SAMPLE[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt8Number FrmOut[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS * MAX_BYTES_PER_SAMPLE + cmsMAXEXTRA * [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_BYTES_PER_SAMPLE[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `cmsMAXEXTRA` is defined [0m[1;39m([0m[39moften [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, that extra multiplication covers [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpossible alpha bytes.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If the code already defines a `MAX_BYTES` or similar macro, reuse it.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Include the new `MAX_BYTES_PER_SAMPLE` macro in `cmsvirt.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor a common [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m next to other constants.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Rebuild and rerun the fuzzer to confirm no stack-buffer-overflow in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Directly addresses** the reported overflow: by matching the buffer size in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsTransform2DeviceLink` to the maximum sample size consumed by [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Preserves existing logic** in UnrollChunkyBytes, so premultiplied-alpha, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel-swapping, and flavor reversal remain unchanged.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Minimal scope**: only alters internal buffer sizes in the one routine that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls the unpacker. No changes to fuzz harness or APIs.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Backward-compatible**: single-byte formats still use only part of the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menlarged buffer. There is no functional change for existing use-cases.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Tests will not break**, since the input format and transformation logic [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain identical; only stack space allocation changes.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Larger stack usage per invocation of `cmsTransform2DeviceLink`, but the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrease is minimal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaximum [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m× the previous `cmsMAXCHANNELS` bytes, typically a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfew dozen more bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that in environments with very high channel counts [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., named-color [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookups[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the new buffer size still fits typical stack limits. If not, consider [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswitching to a small dynamic allocation, but in practice two small arrays of ~[0m[1;36m256[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes each is safe.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References & Similar Patterns  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/cmspack.c`, `UnrollChunkyBytes` now respects `T_BYTES` to read up to [0m[1;36m2[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes/sample. The caller must ensure its buffers reflect that same maximum.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other transforms in LCMS [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., planar unpackers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocate per-channel buffers[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiplied by sample size. This patch brings chunky-path buffer sizing in line with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthose. [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/27/25 23:07:06][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=556506;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=69988;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m5[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.UNCOMPILABLE[1m)[0m                                 [2m               [0m
[2;36m[12/27/25 23:11:37][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.ANALYZE -> TeamStatus.[1;33mPATCH[0m                     ]8;id=874431;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=208786;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations of `FrmIn` and `FrmOut` with fixed‐size arrays using undefined macros [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`cmsMAXCHANNELS`, `cmsMAXEXTRA`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and removed the original `ChansIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`ChansOut` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations. The patch failed to compile, yielding errors about undeclared [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`cmsMAXEXTRA`, `ChansIn`, `ChansOut`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • A fuzzing run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m caused AddressSanitizer to report [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read past the end of a stack buffer in UnrollChunkyBytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmspack.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow originates from cmsTransform2DeviceLink [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsvirt.[0m[1;92mc:1185[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal variables `FrmIn` and `FrmOut` [0m[1;39m([0m[39meach a `cmsUInt32Number`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m do not provide [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msufficient stack space for later unpacking operations.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The sanitizer stack trace shows the overflow reads at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m within the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsTransform2DeviceLink` frame, beyond the small [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte buffer allocated for [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FrmIn`.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `FrmIn` and `FrmOut` are simple [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit values but are later passed to functions[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mUnrollChunkyBytes, CachedXFORM[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that expect larger buffers or higher-bit data per [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The issue surfaces under fuzzing with entropic power schedule and dictionary [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs, indicating that malformed or edge data triggers a code path with larger [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel-byte requirements.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The frame layout in the sanitizer report lists five objects: the overflow [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs in the first one [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`i.i`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, corresponding to `FrmIn` as declared.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • In cmsvirt.c, replaced  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt32Number FrmIn, FrmOut;  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsInt32Number ChansIn, ChansOut;  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    with  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt8Number FrmIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m + cmsMAXEXTRA * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      cmsUInt8Number FrmOut[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcmsMAXCHANNELS * [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m + cmsMAXEXTRA * [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    and removed the `ChansIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`ChansOut` declarations.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The intention was to allocate enough bytes on the stack for up to two bytes per[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plus extra channels.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult after patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Build errors indicating:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `cmsMAXEXTRA` is not declared anywhere.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `ChansIn` and `ChansOut` are still referenced later in the function but no [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlonger declared.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Compilation failed with multiple “undeclared identifier” errors at lines where [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ChansIn`, `ChansOut`, and `cmsMAXEXTRA` are used.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • In src/lcms/src/cmsvirt.c:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – The declaration and intended size of `FrmIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`FrmOut` versus their use in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCOLORSPACE_SH/CHANNELS_SH/BYTES_SH macros.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – The existing definitions of maximum channel counts or other constants that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould guide buffer sizing [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., any `cmsMAXCHANNELS`, `cmsMAXEXTRACHANNELS`, or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – The uses of `ChansIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`ChansOut` for pipeline stage allocation and how [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel count is computed.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • In src/lcms/src/cmspack.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUnrollChunkyBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – The assumptions on input buffer size and how chunk sizes are calculated.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – The mapping between frame formats and buffer allocation.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • In src/lcms/src/cmsxform.c and related transform code:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – How CachedXFORM sets up intermediate buffers and the relationship between [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FrmIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`FrmOut` layouts and the pipeline stages.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Definitions of macros COLORSPACE_SH, CHANNELS_SH, BYTES_SH to understand how [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcombined format codes are built and whether frame variables serve as packed format [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdescriptors rather than data buffers.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis holistic review will clarify the correct sizing strategy for `FrmIn`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`FrmOut` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand identify the proper constants or functions needed to avoid the stack overflow [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout introducing undeclared identifiers.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m239[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m240[0m[39m:    _cmsTRANSFORM* p = [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_cmsTRANSFORM*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Transform;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m241[0m[39m:    cmsStride stride;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m242[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m243[0m[39m:    stride.BytesPerLineIn = BytesPerLineIn;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m244[0m[39m:    stride.BytesPerLineOut = BytesPerLineOut;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m245[0m[39m:    stride.BytesPerPlaneIn = BytesPerPlaneIn;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m246[0m[39m:    stride.BytesPerPlaneOut = BytesPerPlaneOut;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m247[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m248[0m[39m:    p->[0m[1;35mxform[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp, InputBuffer, OutputBuffer, PixelsPerLine, LineCount, &stride[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m249[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m250[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m251[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m252[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m253[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Transform routines [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-----------------------[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m254[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m255[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Float xform converts floats. Since there are no performance issues, one [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutine does all job, including gamut check.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m256[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Note that because extended range, we can use a [0m[1;36m-1.0[0m[39m value for out of gamut [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min this case.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m257[0m[39m:static[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m258[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mFloatXFORM[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_cmsTRANSFORM* p,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m259[0m[39m:                const void* in,[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m260[0m[39m:                void* out, [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmspcs.[0m[1;92mc:1[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m200[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:       CIE [0m[1;92m15:2004[0m[39m CIELab is defined as:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:       L* = [0m[1;36m116[0m[39m*[0m[1;35mf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mY/Yn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m                     [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m <= L* <= [0m[1;36m100[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m:       a* = [0m[1;36m500[0m[39m*[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;35mf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mX/Xn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;35mf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mY/Yn[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m][0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m:       b* = [0m[1;36m200[0m[39m*[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;35mf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mY/Yn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;35mf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZ/Zn[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m][0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m:       and[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m:              [0m[1;35mf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m = t^[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m                     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m >= t >  [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m24[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m^[0m[1;36m3[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m:                     [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m841[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m*t + [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m16[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m      [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m <= t <= [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m24[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m^[0m[1;36m3[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:       Reverse transform is:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m:       X = Xn*[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ma* [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m500[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mL* + [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m][0m[39m ^ [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mX/Xn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m24[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:         = Xn*[0m[1;39m([0m[39ma* [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m500[0m[39m + L* [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m7.787[0m[39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mX/Xn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m <= [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m24[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m116[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:       PCS in Lab2 is encoded as:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:              [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bit Lab PCS:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:                     L*      [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m into a [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..ff byte.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:                     a*      t + [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m range is [0m[1;36m-128.0[0m[39m  +[0m[1;36m127.0[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:                     b*[0m                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:                     L*     [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m  into a [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..ff00 word.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:                     a*     t + [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m  range is  [0m[1;36m-128.0[0m[39m  +[0m[1;36m127.9961[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:                     b*[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:Interchange Space   Component     Actual Range        Encoded Range[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m69:C[0m[39mIE XYZ             X             [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m -> [0m[1;36m1.99997[0m[39m        [0m[1;36m0x0000[0m[39m -> [0m[1;36m0xffff[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m70:C[0m[39mIE XYZ             Y             [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m -> [0m[1;36m1.99997[0m[39m        [0m[1;36m0x0000[0m[39m -> [0m[1;36m0xffff[0m           [2m                [0m
